{"article_id":"jA8zq56n9h6KwDGp","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"HANOI , Vietnam -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"President Trump ' s high-stakes summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong-un ended abruptly without a deal Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"cutting short two days of talks","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"aimed at dismantling Pyongyang ' s weapons program","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"and leaving the two sides with a murky and uncertain path ahead .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"In the stunning outcome in the Vietnamese capital of Hanoi , the two sides disagreed over what led to the breakdown and whether and when new talks can be arranged .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Mr. Trump said","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"he expected his extraordinary personal diplomacy with Mr. Kim","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"to end the crisis on the divided Korean Peninsula","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"will continue .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"To the surprise of supporters and detractors back home , Mr. Trump proved willing to walk away from a diplomatic breakthrough","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that he clearly craved .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"he ended the private talks two hours early","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"when Mr. Kim insisted","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"that all international economic sanctions be dropped","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"before the North agrees to shutter its nuclear and missile programs .","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"\" Sometimes you have to walk , \"","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Mr. Trump explained at a subdued closing news conference .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Mr. Trump said","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"he rejected a more modest agreement","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"that was \" ready to be signed , \"","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"and a signing ceremony and celebratory lunch","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"that were on the two leaders ' schedules","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"were quickly scrubbed .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"\" I ' d much rather do it right","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"than do it fast ... , \"","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Trump said .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"\" Basically , they wanted the sanctions lifted in their entirety","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":",","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"and we couldn ' t do that . \"","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told reporters","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"as he flew to the Philippines from Vietnam on Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"\" We were hoping","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"we could take another big swing","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"when the two leaders got together .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Trump says","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"at least Cohen didn ' t lie about Russian collusion :","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"' It was pretty shameful '","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"\" We made some progress ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"but we didn ' t get as far","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"as we would have hoped","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"we would have gotten , \"","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Mr. Pompeo said .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"But in a sign of possible trouble ahead , North Korea ' s top diplomat held a rare press briefing of his own","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"to challenge Mr. Trump ' s version of events .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Mr. Kim had not made the maximalist demands","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that Mr. Trump described .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Even as the U.S. delegation was jetting home on Air Force One ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"North Korean Foreign Minister Ri Yong-ho insisted","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"that Pyongyang had asked only for a partial easing of the sanctions in exchange for shutting down the North ' s main nuclear complex in Yongbyon .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Mr. Ri said","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"the North was also ready to offer in writing a permanent halt of the country ' s nuclear and intercontinental ballistic missile tests","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"and that Washington had wasted an opportunity","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"that \" may not come again . \"","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"Mr. Pompeo predicted","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that lower-level diplomacy between the two sides could resume quickly ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"but Pyongyang challenged even that .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"North Korean Vice Foreign Minister Choe Son-hui told reporters","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"that Mr. Kim was finding it difficult to understand why the U.S. left the talks","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"and that the young North Korean leader \" may have lost his will \"","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"to continue the talks .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Mr. Trump said","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"the end of the talks was amicable .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"He even offered a sort of defense of Mr. Kim over the death of U.S. college student Otto Warmbier ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"who succumbed to severe illness shortly after his release from a North Korean prison in June 2017 .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"Mr. Trump once cited Warmbier ' s treatment as a symbol of the human rights failings of the Kim regime ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"but he said Thursday","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"that the North Korean leader told him","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"he had not been aware of the Ohio college student ' s case .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"Mr. Kim \" tells me","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"that he didn ' t know about it ,","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"and I will take him at his word , \"","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"Mr. Trump said .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Those comments struck a discordant note in the generally positive assessment in Washington of Mr. Trump ' s handling of the summit .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"\" We must remember Otto ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"and we should never let North Korea off the hook for what they did to him , \"","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Sen . Rob Portman , Ohio Republican , said in a statement .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"But ending the summit","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"without agreement on any of the issues","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"discussed","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"clearly fell short of expectations .","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"Negotiators on both sides had spent months in talks","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"leading up to the summit ,","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"trying to pave the way for an agreement","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"that also could have included a declaration","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"to formally end the Korean War or the opening of a U.S. liaison office in Pyongyang .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"The stunning result divided analysts","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"who said","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"Mr. Trump had already taken a huge gamble","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"in agreeing to meet with the reclusive North Korean leader","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"and holding a one-on-negotiating session with so many key items still unresolved .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Charles E. Schumer , a New York Democrat","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"who is usually a fierce critic of the president ,","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"Mr. Trump \" did the right thing","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"by walking away","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"and not cutting a poor deal for the sake of a photo op . \"","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi , California Democrat , also said","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"Mr. Trump was right not to take a bad deal ,","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"but she argued","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"that Mr. Kim was the \" big winner \"","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"for having secured two personal summits with an American president","depth":15},{"id":105,"text":"and easing his country ' s pariah status","depth":16},{"id":106,"text":"without having made any significant concessions .","depth":16},{"id":107,"text":"Some said","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"Mr. Trump may have enhanced his bargaining position","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"by showing the North Koreans and a watching world","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"that he was willing to risk short-term setbacks","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"to achieve his long-term goals .","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"North Korea ' s hopes for an easing of its economic isolation","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"- and even a possible formal ending to the stalemated Korean War of the 1950s -","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"were dashed with Mr. Trump ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"to walk away .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"The summit result was clearly a setback for South Korea ,","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"which has pursued its own rapprochement with Pyongyang","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"and hoped","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"a U.S.-North Korean detente would speed along that process .","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"Mr. Trump spoke with South Korean President Moon Jae-in on the flight home from Hanoi ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"the White House said .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"Mr. Moon ' s office said in a statement","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"that it regretted the outcome of the summit","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"but expressed a firm commitment","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"to continue North-South negotiations .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"South Korean officials said","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"Mr . Moon encouraged Mr. Trump to continue his efforts","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"for accomplishing the \" historic feat","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"of resolving the world ' s last remaining Cold War rivalry \"","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"and that the two leaders agreed to meet soon","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"to discuss the nuclear issue ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"The Associated Press reported .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"China , North Korea ' s longtime key ally , refused to assign blame for the Hanoi summit .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"Officials said","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"Mr. Trump ' s diplomatic gambit was a positive step","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"and that the U.S. and North Korea must \" meet each other halfway \"","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"if a deal is to be struck .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Lu Kang told reporters","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"that the Korean Peninsula had experienced a significant \" turnaround \" over the past year , a \" hard-won result \"","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"that is worth cherishing .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"After a friendly dinner Wednesday night in Hanoi and talks","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"that Mr. Trump described as \" very good , \"","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"the discussions rapidly fell apart Thursday .","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"The two leaders canceled a formal working lunch ,","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"and the White House soon announced a \" schedule change. \"","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"Word soon came down","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"that the joint signing ceremony with both leaders was canceled .","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"The second summit between the two men began with smiles and handshakes Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"as Mr. Trump sought more clarity from the North Korean leader on the steps","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"he would be willing to take","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"to dismantle his nuclear weapons program .","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"They started that process at a breakthrough summit in Singapore in June .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"Mr. Trump was lowering expectations for the second round of talks ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"cautioning the media","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"that he was in \" no rush \" to get a comprehensive agreement","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"as long as Mr. Kim continued to honor his pledge","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"not to conduct any more missile tests .","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"Asked","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"whether he was serious about giving up his weapons program ,","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"Mr. Kim had said ,","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"\" If I was not ,","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"I wouldn ' t be here . \"","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"Another reporter asked","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"whether he was willing to take concrete steps","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"to denuclearize .","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"Mr. Kim said :","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"\" That ' s what we are discussing right now . \" ⦁","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"David R. Sands reported from Washington for this article ,","depth":3},{"id":169,"text":"which is based in part on wire service reports .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":339,"left":0,"right":338,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":338,"left":336,"right":337,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":336,"left":248,"right":335,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":248,"left":213,"right":247,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":213,"left":199,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":178,"right":198,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":174,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":173,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":1,"right":172,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":171,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":6,"right":176,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":175,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":7,"right":8,"rel